      "created": "2014-04-28T02:14:45.770+0000",
      "description": "Allocation of Large Containers are notoriously problematic, as smaller containers can more easily grab resources. \n\nThe proposal for this JIRA is to maintain a map of container sizes, and time-to-allocation, that can be used as:\n* general insight on cluster behavior, \n* to inform the reservation-system, and allows us to \"account for delays\" in allocation, so that the user reservation is respected regardless the size of containers requested.\n\n\n",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/resolution/6",
        "id": "6",
        "description": "The problem isn't valid and it can't be fixed.",
        "name": "Invalid"
      },
